public class ModuleFrame
extends javax.swing.JInternalFrame
implements java.beans.PropertyChangeListener, javax.swing.event.InternalFrameListener

An internal frame designed specifically for holding Module objects. Every visible Module should run within an ModuleFrame, and is supplied to it upon construction.

Construct a new frame around the given module and display.

Parameters:
module - The module to feed to the frame
centre - Should the frame be centred?
honourSize - Should we respect the frame's preferred size or should we override it with the default?
resizable - Is the frame allowed to be resized?

setSizeAndLocation

public static void setSizeAndLocation(javax.swing.JInternalFrame frame,
                                      javax.swing.JDesktopPane desktop,
                                      boolean centre,
                                      boolean honourSize)
Set the size and location of any frame, taking care of out of bounds frames. This method has been made static to help any internal frames size themselves as if they were a proper Venice ModuleFrame.

Parameters:
frame - the frame to size
desktop - the desktop
centre - whether the frame should be centred?
honourSize - whether we should honour the frame's preferred size
